creator: Felgo
descriptionHtml:
Felgo & QML Live Scripting is a viewer app to try out Felgo and Qt, without installing the Felgo SDK.

Write your QML scripts at
https://felgo.com/web-editor-android/
in your browser and view the result immediately in this app, no re-build required! The app with your script code is reloaded on-the-fly when you make a change in the browser.

This feature is completely free to use, no registration required.

To download the free Felgo SDK and start building native mobile apps, go to
http://felgo.com/

Felgo is based on the Qt framework. Qt is a powerful cross-platform toolkit based on C++ which enables powerful animations with Qt Quick and native performance on all major mobile platforms.

Felgo extends the Qt 5 framework with components that you can test with this app. These are for example: 
- Components that allow native user experience on all major mobile platforms with a single code base. E.g. on iOS you will experience swipe back gesture support, while on Android a navigation drawer is used – this is supported automatically without any change of code. 
- Full range of native widgets optimized for a native platform behavior like tabs, dialogs and list views.

Felgo allows native user experience with a single code base and fluid animations.
You can download it together with the full source code of this app for free at
http://felgo.com/
descriptionShort: Write QML code in your browser and view the result live on your mobile device.

title: Felgo & QML Live Scripting

creator: Felgo
descriptionHtml:

DEVELOP

The Projects viewer allows you to develop Felgo apps & games on your desktop, and view the result in real-time on your device, without installing mobile SDKs.

Boost your productivity, by saving time on compilation and deployment.

Try 20+ included app demos like music streaming apps, social apps, workout apps & more. Every demo comes with full source code and documentation to improve your development skills.

The 200+ included app examples show how to use Qt and Felgo components in your app.


REFERENCE

Browse through all available Felgo and Qt APIs and open documentation, examples & related content.

The included search shows you relevant demos, examples & components for every keyword you look for.
